messages.subject: Re: [AlwaysLearning] wedding photos
messages.msgSnippet: Oh girl, you do not want to go there .  Give me an inch and that whole site will be nothin but me and the kin. I found a picture of me a couple months ago
messages.messageBody:
Oh girl, you do not want to go there <g>. Give me an inch and that whole
site will be nothin but me and the kin.

I found a picture of me a couple months ago and it is the same age Dana is
right now, everyone who looks at it says "what a cute picture of Dana", they
can't believe the resemblance when I say it is me.

I do have some pics of Joe and I on our wedding day with the girls, they
look so sweet and innocent(they were 8 and 6 when we married). There were
some tough days when I thought I made the biggest mistake being a
stepmother, but then I remember how much I love them and it all goes away.

sistakammi


> OK, Dan took up my challenge and posted a photo from our wedding. Can you

No
> kid yet. Hmmmmm, correlation? Come on, someone else do this too or I'll
> feel silly.
>
> Jocelyn
> (it was December, 1985)

messages.messageBody:
OK, Dan took up my challenge and posted a photo from our wedding. Can you
tell from the giant glasses what the year was? No gray hair and skinny. No
kid yet. Hmmmmm, correlation? Come on, someone else do this too or I'll
feel silly.

Jocelyn
(it was December, 1985)
